title.narrative: New Element

description.narrative: As part of the plans to take the Life Skills Education programme to scale, UNICEF Indonesia supported the Ministry of Education and Culture to digitalize the teacher training component. This work, together with the findings from the 21st century skills and entrepreneurship pilot, have formed the evidence base for shaping the work around Reimagine Education in Indonesia, helping to prioritise the areas for UNICEF’s involvement and technical support. 21st century skills development, adolescent empowerment and digital learning will be among key priorities in the next country programme. | Status:Met | As-of Date:30/11/2020
